        "subheading": "",
        "title": "<p><em>How They Are Made</em></p>",
        "description": "<p>Laboratory Grown Diamonds are formed using two primary methods:</p><ul><li><strong>High Pressure High Temperature (HPHT)</strong></li><li><strong>Chemical Vapour Deposition (CVD) </strong></li></ul><p>At Natalie Marie Jewellery, we offer both, ensuring all stones are certified by either the International Gemmological Institute (IGI) or the Gemmological Institute of America (GIA).<br/></p><p>The journey of a laboratory grown diamond is complex and multi-staged:<br/></p><ol><li>Grown in a laboratory</li><li>Cut and polished (often in a separate facility)</li><li>Certified by an independent gemological institute</li><li>Sold through the global market</li><li>Selected by a jeweller</li></ol><p>Like natural diamonds, this journey can involve multiple stages and locations, which can impact traceability.</p>",
        "colour_style": "dark",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_1_link": "",
        "button_style": "underline"
      }
    },
    "5745a96a-89f1-43ff-b4e6-2d5a49f7d900": {
      "type": "text-with-media",
      "blocks": {
        "template--16125431546025__5745a96a-89f1-43ff-b4e6-2d5a49f7d900-1682331895cf99bbfc-0": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Clarity.webp"
